body:
## Summary

This patch fixes simulation hangs when calling interface functions through
virtual interfaces in designs with multiple interface instances.

V3Scope maps interface function clones via `user2p` which is overwritten by
each scope clone (last-one-wins). For direct hierarchical calls this is harmless
because V3LinkDot re-resolves `taskp()` through the cell path. Virtual interface
MethodCalls instead retain the `user2p` mapping, so inlining bakes in VarScope
references from an arbitrary clone. Subsequent passes then fold affected
expressions to constants, causing simulation to hang.

Discovered while running the UVM testbench on cv32e40p (core-v-verif) https://github.com/openhwgroup/core-v-verif/pull/2724 .

## Reproducer

```systemverilog
interface my_if;
  logic clk = 0;
  bit   clk_active = 0;
  initial begin
    wait (clk_active);
    forever #5 clk = ~clk;
  end
  function void start_clk();
    clk_active = 1;
  endfunction
endinterface

class Driver;
  virtual my_if vif;
  task run();
    #10;
    vif.start_clk();
  endtask
endclass

module t;
  my_if intf();
  my_if intf_unused();  // second instance triggers the bug
  initial begin
    automatic Driver d = new;
    d.vif = intf;
    d.run();
    repeat (4) @(posedge intf.clk);
    $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```

On master (compiles without errors, simulation hangs indefinitely):

```
- Verilator: Walltime 0.004 s (elab=0.000, cvt=0.000, bld=0.004); cpu 0.001 s on 1 threads; allocated 24.375 MB
        obj_vlt/t_interface_virtual_func_wait/Vt_interface_virtual_func_wait    > obj_vlt/t_interface_virtual_func_wait/vlt_sim.log
==SUMMARY: Left 1  Passed 0  Failed 0  Running 1  Time 0:15
(no output -- simulation never completes)
```

## Changes

- `TaskStateVisitor::visit(AstNodeFTask*)`: force `noInline` for interface
  functions when `hasVirtIfaces()`, preventing wrong-instance VarScope refs
  from being baked in.
- `TaskVisitor::visit(AstNodeFTask*)`: suppress false IMPURE warning for
  interface functions (interface member access is not truly external).
  Also fix "recursvie" typo in the original comment.

## Test

- Added `test_regress/t/t_interface_virtual_func_wait.{v,py}` -- virtual
  interface calls interface function that enables a clock; verifies
  simulation completes without hang.

